Add a `CHANGELOG_AUTO.md` generator script to the Forever library. Create `scripts/generate-changelog.js` that automatically builds a structured changelog from the git commit history. Requirements: 1) Parse commits using Node.js `child_process.execSync` to run `git log` with a custom format. 2) Group commits by conventional commit type: feat, fix, perf, refactor, docs, chore, test. 3) For each group, list the commit message, short SHA, and date. 4) Output a well-formatted markdown file `CHANGELOG_AUTO.md` at the repo root. 5) Add a `"changelog"` script to `package.json` that runs `node scripts/generate-changelog.js`. 6) The script should accept an optional `--since` flag (e.g. `--since v1.0.0`) to only include commits after a specific tag or SHA. 7) Add a `--format json` flag that also exports the same data as `scripts/changelog.json`. 8) Write tests in `tests/changelog.test.js` that mock `child_process.execSync` and verify that commits are correctly parsed and grouped into the expected markdown and JSON structures.